GET '/categories/<int:category_id>/questions'
- Fetches a list of questions in a specific category in which the query takes the category_id as the filter 
- Request Arguments: category_id
- Returns: An object displaying the single key:value pair of the referenced category. It also returns each object in the list of filtered questions showing questions, answer, category_id, question_id, difficulty and an object showing the total number of questions in that category.  
{
  "current_category": 1,
  "questions": [
    {
      "answer": "The Liver",
      "category": 1,
      "difficulty": 4,
      "id": 20,
      "question": "What is the heaviest organ in the human body?"
    },
    {
      "answer": "Alexander Fleming",
      "category": 1,
      "difficulty": 3,
      "id": 21,
      "question": "Who discovered penicillin?"
    },
    {
      "answer": "Blood",
      "category": 1,
      "difficulty": 4,
      "id": 22,
      "question": "Hematology is a branch of medicine involving the study of what?"
    },
    {
      "answer": "Quarks",
      "category": 1,
      "difficulty": 4,
      "id": 29,
      "question": "What are considered to be the building blocks of hadrons?"
    }
  ],
  "success": true,
  "total": 4
}

