POST '/questions/search'
- Takes in an object of the form "searchTerm": "input" as a key value pair. 
- Request Arguments: None
- Returns: An object displaying the single key:value pair of the referenced category which will be NULL as we search using string input. It also returns each object in the list of matching questions showing questions, answer, category_id, question_id, difficulty and an object showing the total number of questions matching the search term.  
{
  "current_category": null, 
  "questions": [
    {
      "answer": "Edward Scissorhands", 
      "category": 5, 
      "difficulty": 3, 
      "id": 6, 
      "question": "What was the title of the 1990 fantasy directed by Tim Burton about a young man with multi-bladed appendages?"
    }, 
    {
      "answer": "Escher", 
      "category": 2, 
      "difficulty": 1, 
      "id": 16, 
      "question": "Which Dutch graphic artist\u2013initials M C was a creator of optical illusions?"
    }, 
    {
      "answer": "Jackson Pollock", 
      "category": 2, 
      "difficulty": 2, 
      "id": 19, 
      "question": "Which American artist was a pioneer of Abstract Expressionism, and a leading exponent of action painting?"
    }
  ], 
  "success": true, 
  "total_questions": 3
}

POST '/quizzes'
- Takes in an object containing a list of previously asked questions and a quiz_category object with key value pairs with the category type and category ID. The form presents as {"previous_questions":[],"quiz_category":{"type":"Science","id":"1"}}
- Request Arguments: None
- Returns: A question object containing the question, answer, category_id, difficulty and the questiond_id. 
{
  "question": {
    "answer": "Alexander Fleming", 
    "category": 1, 
    "difficulty": 3, 
    "id": 21, 
    "question": "Who discovered penicillin?"
  }, 
  "success": true
}

## Testing
To run the tests locally, run
```
python test_app.py
```